reviews.review_text: Excellent Recording Pigpen's tracks are especially appreciated.

- An excellent Other One (this is the one on "Skullfuck"); otherwise a fairly good show. I think they tried to play the whole That's It suite in the interest of the live album, but the Cryptical 1 wasn't good enough to include. The whole show is not nearly as good as two nights previous, though the Dark Star certainly is pretty good. 

When I first bought "Skullfuck" I had only seen the Dead at Autzen Stadium and had never heard of the Fillmore, so my mental image of "the Grateful Dead live in '71" was basically a younger version of them playing at some place like Autzen: a big outdoor show. The fact that the Fillmore is actually a pretty tiny, intimate indoor space says a lot about the Dead's sound system. The '71 live album (and all these Fillmore shows) has a sound that is unbelievably spacious, and though their '71 sound is very hard-edged and brittle for my taste, lacking the warmth of the 73-74 sound, it already had an amazingly open feel to it.
